decks.notes: The key concept of this deck is to generate mana quickly and efficiently using cards like Baral, Chief of Compliance and Goblin Electromancer, while also utilizing spells like Desperate Ritual, Pyretic Ritual, and Manamorphose to generate even more mana. The deck aims to chain spells together, using cards like Gifts Ungiven, Merchant Scroll, and Past in Flames to set up powerful combos and deal a large amount of damage with cards like Grapeshot. The deck also includes card selection and draw spells like Serum Visions and Sleight of Hand to help find the necessary pieces for the combo.

The core strategy of this deck is to ramp up its mana quickly using cards like Amulet of Vigor, Sakura-Tribe Scout, and Azusa, Lost but Seeking, allowing for explosive plays and fast mana generation. The key combo involves utilizing Primeval Titan to search for and put into play lands like Vesuva and Castle Garenbrig, generating immense mana advantage. Additionally, the deck includes utility lands like Ghost Quarter and Bojuka Bog to disrupt opponents' strategies. Ultimately, the deck aims to overwhelm opponents with a powerful board presence and win the game through its efficient combo plays.

This deck focuses on quickly assembling the pieces needed to ramp up mana and play Primeval Titan. By utilizing cards like Amulet of Vigor and Azusa, Lost but Seeking, the deck can generate a large amount of mana and search for key lands such as Field of the Dead. Once Primeval Titan is in play, it can search for additional lands and put pressure on the opponent by generating tokens or dealing direct damage. The deck also includes tools for protection and disruption, such as Pact of Negation and Engineered Explosives.

The main concept of this deck is to aggressively deal as much damage to the opponent as quickly as possible using efficient burn spells and fast creatures like Goblin Guide and Monastery Swiftspear. The deck aims to keep the pressure on the opponent by consistently dealing damage, while also utilizing cards like Eidolon of the Great Revel to punish the opponent for casting spells. The mana base is built to support a high density of red spells and enable consistent early game aggression.

The deck focuses on quickly dropping your own life total in order to power up Death's Shadow and other creatures, while disrupting your opponent's game plan with hand disruption spells like Inquisition of Kozilek and Thoughtseize. The deck also includes cards like Tarmogoyf and Temur Battle Rage to deal massive damage quickly. With a mix of efficient removal spells and powerful threats, the goal is to apply constant pressure on your opponent and close out the game before they can stabilize.

The main focus of this deck is to rapidly fill up the graveyard with cards like Bloodghast, Narcomoeba, and Prized Amalgam using cards like Cathartic Reunion and Life from the Loam. By dredging cards like Stinkweed Imp and Golgari Thug, the player can trigger powerful graveyard synergies like Creeping Chill and Conflagrate. This combo-based strategy aims to overwhelm the opponent with a constant stream of threats from the graveyard, utilizing cards like Shriekhorn and Merchant of the Vale to set up the graveyard quickly and efficiently.

This deck focuses on putting pressure on the opponent with fast, aggressive creatures like Reality Smasher and Thought-Knot Seer. It also utilizes mana acceleration from cards like Noble Hierarch and Eldrazi Temple to play threats ahead of schedule. Stoneforge Mystic helps to find important equipment like Batterskull and Sword of Feast and Famine, providing additional advantage. Additionally, the deck includes disruptive elements like Eldrazi Displacer to control the opponent's board state. The color fixing from lands like Cavern of Souls and Horizon Canopy ensures consistent mana production for these powerful plays.

The deck revolves around utilizing artifacts and combo pieces such as Jeskai Ascendancy, Paradoxical Outcome and Urza, Lord High Artificer to generate mana and draw cards, while also benefiting from the synergies of Emry, Lurker of the Loch and Mox Opal. The deck aims to quickly assemble its combo pieces to generate infinite mana, pump up its creatures, and trigger various abilities to overwhelm the opponent and win the game in a single explosive turn. It also includes some control elements and protection spells to ensure the combo can be executed successfully.

The main concept of this deck is to assemble a powerful combo using creatures to tutor for specific pieces and create a strong board presence. Utilizing cards like Eldritch Evolution, Finale of Devastation, and Once Upon a Time, the deck aims to quickly find key creatures like Devoted Druid and Vizier of Remedies to generate infinite mana and combo off. Support cards like Giver of Runes and Shalai, Voice of Plenty protect the combo while Eldadamri's Call and Eladamri's Call help tutor for necessary pieces. The deck's toolbox nature allows for adaptability and resilience against various strategies.

The deck focuses on quickly lowering your life total in order to make Death's Shadow a powerful threat on the battlefield. Using cards like Street Wraith and Mishra's Bauble to draw cards and Thoughtseize and Inquisition of Kozilek to disrupt your opponent's hand, while also utilizing various removal spells to clear the way for your aggressive creatures. The inclusion of Snapcaster Mage allows for additional value and flexibility in the deck, while Stubborn Denial provides a strong form of counter magic to protect your key threats.

The main concept of this deck is to overwhelm the opponent with a fast and aggressive strategy using human creatures. By playing powerful cards like Champion of the Parish, Reflector Mage, and Thalia's Lieutenant, the deck aims to quickly build a board presence and disrupt the opponent's game plan. Aether Vial is used to cheat out creatures and maintain pressure throughout the game. The deck's mana base supports the tribal theme with lands like Cavern of Souls and Ancient Ziggurat. Ultimately, the goal is to outpace the opponent and secure a victory through sheer aggression and synergy.

The deck focuses on utilizing Jeskai Ascendancy to create a powerful combo engine. By playing cheap artifacts and creatures like Emry, Lurker of the Loch and Sai, Master Thopterist, the deck can generate mana and draw cards while triggering Jeskai Ascendancy's ability to untap creatures and pump them up. With cards like Urza, Lord High Artificer and Paradoxical Outcome, the deck can quickly generate a large amount of mana and card advantage to overwhelm opponents. This combo-centric strategy aims to win the game through explosive turns and overwhelming the opponent with a flurry of spells and creatures.

The deck focuses on controlling the game through a combination of counter spells, discard spells, removal, and powerful threats. It aims to disrupt the opponent's game plan with cards like Inquisition of Kozilek, Thoughtseize, and Collective Brutality while also generating card advantage with cards like Lingering Souls and Jace, Vryn's Prodigy. The deck has a strong late-game plan with powerful threats like Obzedat, Ghost Council and Geist of Saint Traft. Additionally, it has the capability to combo off with Goryo's Vengeance to bring back powerful creatures from the graveyard for a fast win.

The main concept of this Control - UrzaTron deck is to assemble Urza's Mine, Power Plant, and Tower to generate a large amount of mana and cast powerful threats like Wurmcoil Engine, Thragtusk, and Emrakul, the Promised End. The deck also utilizes cards like Karn Liberated and Karn, the Great Creator to control the board and disrupt the opponent's game plan. The deck focuses on ramping up quickly and overwhelming the opponent with big threats while maintaining control of the battlefield.

The deck focuses on assembling the UrzaTron lands (Urza's Tower, Power Plant, and Mine) to generate massive amounts of mana. This mana is used to play powerful threats like Wurmcoil Engine, Thragtusk, and Ulamog, the Ceaseless Hunger. The deck also includes a variety of ways to search for and tutor the UrzaTron lands, as well as removal spells like Karn Liberated and Ugin, the Spirit Dragon to control the board. The control aspect of the deck is further emphasized by cards like Blast Zone and Oblivion Ring to deal with opposing threats.

The deck focuses on controlling the game through counterspells, removal spells, and bounce effects while generating card advantage with cards like Jace, the Mind Sculptor, Teferi, Time Raveler, and Snapcaster Mage. It also utilizes a Stoneforge Mystic package to search for equipment like Batterskull and Sword of Feast and Famine to provide additional threats and value. The manabase is designed to support the control elements of the deck while also providing access to powerful utility lands like Field of Ruin and Mystic Sanctuary.
